title: Kiss - Roanoke, VA 1979-07-10 FLAC
description:
Kiss
Roanoke Civic Center
Roanoke, VA
July 10, 1979
Dynasty Tour

FLAC - audience recording (Incomplete)


In the spirit of Christmas as well as to celebrate the induction of Kiss into the R&R Hall of Fame, I thought I'd share a rare, unreleased recording. This one comes from Roanoke, Virginia during the early part of the Dynasty Tour. It includes the 4 tracks that were played from all 4 solo albums and cuts off right after Peter's "Tossin' and Turnin'".


Setlist (incomplete):

King of the Night Time World
Radioactive
Move On
Calling Dr. Love
Firehouse
New York Groove
I Was Made For Lovin' You
Love Gun
2,000 Man/Ace Frehley Guitar Solo
Tossin' And Turnin'


Happy Holidays!
